bayou.jtype

Interface TypeArg

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArrayType, ClassType, IntersectionType, NullType, ReferenceType, TypeVar, Wildcard

    public interface TypeArg
    Type argument.

    A type argument is either a ReferenceType or a Wildcard.

    For example 

        TypeArg K = ClassType.of(String.class);
    TypeArg V = Wildcard.extends_(Number.class);

    JavaType<?> type = ClassType.of(Map.class, K, V); // Map<String, ? extends Number>

    • Method Summary

      Abstract Method

      A textual description of the type argument.
